OL,6,GLast week we discussed the urgent need
OL,7,Gto find ways of offering more HD
OL,8,Gchannels on Freeview.
OL,10,FIf this doesn't happen, sooner or later
OL,11,Fterrestrial television will become a
OL,12,Flegacy service ` the equivalent of
OL,13,Fanalogue TV 15 years ago or 405-line
OL,14,Ftransmissions in 1980.
OL,16,FIn the past week, the situation has
OL,17,Ftaken an interesting turn. The BBC's
OL,18,Fmove to an all-HD satellite service has
OL,19,Fbeen accelerated.
OL,3,CSky/Freesat changes leaving Freeview in
OL,4,Cthe dust
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S      G1/9
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
PN,34302
SC,0002
PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F343A1675172173
OL,6,FIn less than a month, all English
OL,7,Fregions, BBC Alba, BBC Parliament and
OL,8,Fthe red button service will be in HD on
OL,9,FSky and Freesat.
OL,11,FIt would not be completely surprising
OL,12,Fif the SD "Nightlight" service ends up
OL,13,Fbeing switched off a little earlier
OL,14,Fthan currently anticipated.
OL,16,FIt will also be interesting to see
OL,17,Fwhether SD Nightlight remains on HD
OL,18,Felectronic programme guides for long.
OL,3,CSky/Freesat changes leaving Freeview in
OL,4,Cthe dust
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S      G2/9
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
PN,34303
SC,0003
PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F343A1675172173
OL,6,FWhat matters is ensuring that those
OL,7,Fwith SD equipment get sufficient notice
OL,8,Fand that help is available for the
OL,9,Fvulnerable.
OL,11,FSo will the BBC's move be copied by
OL,12,Fother broadcasters? I suspect the days
OL,13,Fof SD variants of HD channels will soon
OL,14,Fbe over.
OL,16,FITV no longer has SD versions of most
OL,17,Fof its regions on satellite ` the SD
OL,18,Fservice which remains is principally a
OL,19,Fnightlight except in the Border
OL,20,FScotland and Channel regions.
OL,3,CSky/Freesat changes leaving Freeview in
OL,4,Cthe dust
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S      G3/9
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
PN,34304
SC,0004
PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F343A1675172173
OL,6,FOn Freesat, ITV 2, 3 and 4 recently
OL,7,Fmoved to HD and the SD versions are no
OL,8,Flonger on the EPG.
OL,10,FClosing the remaining SD streams would
OL,11,Fpotentially allow these two regions
OL,12,Fand, perhaps, ITVBe and CITV to move to
OL,13,FHD.
OL,15,FThe +1 services, which are declining in
OL,16,Fimportance through catch-up, might
OL,17,Fstill be SD only but could probably be
OL,18,Fsqueezed onto an HD-enabled multiplex.
OL,3,CSky/Freesat changes leaving Freeview in
OL,4,Cthe dust
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S      G4/9
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
PN,34305
SC,0005
PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F343A1675172173
OL,6,FSimilar questions apply to Channel 4
OL,7,Fwhich, strangely, still has not moved
OL,8,Fits full regionalised service on to 104
OL,9,Fon Freesat, several months after it
OL,10,Fbecame available on Sky.
OL,12,FBut surely Channel 4 will not wait much
OL,13,Flonger and won't want to run a number
OL,14,Fof SD streams of its main service
OL,15,Findefinitely? Will Channel 4 also,
OL,16,Feventually, make the HD versions of its
OL,17,Fother channels free-to-view?
OL,19,FUltimately a lot depends on Sky
OL,20,Fcontracts.
OL,3,CSky/Freesat changes leaving Freeview in
OL,4,Cthe dust
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S      G5/9
