PN,34306
SC,0006
PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F343A1675172173
OL,6,FWhen the HD service was considered a
OL,7,Fpremium, there were many examples of
OL,8,Fchannels which provided an unencrypted
OL,9,FSD service and an HD service behind a
OL,10,Fpaywall ` even if this paywall was
OL,11,Fsometimes just the basic HD
OL,12,Fsubscription.
OL,14,FBut is it still worth some channels
OL,15,Fpaying for both HD and SD streams? I
OL,16,Fsuspect some will have to decide
OL,17,Fbetween making their HD service
OL,18,Ffree-to-air and withdrawing from
OL,19,FFreesat.
OL,3,CSky/Freesat changes leaving Freeview in
OL,4,Cthe dust
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S      G6/9
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
PN,34307
SC,0007
PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F343A1675172173
OL,6,FEither way it seems certain Freesat
OL,7,Fwill continue to offer much more HD
OL,8,Fwhich is free at the point of use.
OL,10,FStreaming services also offer HD and
OL,11,FUHD. Meanwhile Freeview is only set for
OL,12,Fmodest boosts.
OL,14,FBBC One's English regions will soon be
OL,15,Fin HD on Freeview but not, it seems,
OL,16,Fthe full suite of ITV regions. None of
OL,17,Fthe other extra BBC HD services will be
OL,18,Favailable.
OL,3,CSky/Freesat changes leaving Freeview in
OL,4,Cthe dust
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S      G7/9
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
PN,34308
SC,0008
PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F343A1675172173
OL,6,FHowever an extra SD channel is set to
OL,7,Fappear on the Freeview light service
OL,8,Fwhere more efficient encoding has
OL,9,Fcreated some space.
OL,11,FIt still is not clear what channel will
OL,12,Fgo there but the obvious suggestions
OL,13,Finclude 4Seven, E4 Extra and ITVBe. (It
OL,14,Fis still not known publicly whether the
OL,15,Fslot outside Wales belongs to ITV or
OL,16,FChannel 4.)
OL,3,CSky/Freesat changes leaving Freeview in
OL,4,Cthe dust
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S      G8/9
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
PN,34309
SC,0009
PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F343A1675172173
OL,6,FStill, the more efficient encoding
OL,7,Fcould mean a slightly poorer SD picture
OL,8,F` not a problem on a small set but
OL,9,Fpotentially an issue for the discerning
OL,10,Fviewer on a 42-inch set.
OL,12,FIt is good news for Freeview light
OL,13,Fviewers. But it's hardly enough by
OL,14,Fitself to futureproof terrestrial TV.
OL,16,FUrgent action is needed. Time to
OL,17,Fconvert more multiplexes to the newer
OL,18,FHD-enabled standard.
OL,3,CSky/Freesat changes leaving Freeview in
